other_tests.findings: The appendix is air-filled proximally but distally is fluid-filled and dilated in caliber. Mild atherosclerotic disease is noted. The urinary bladder, distal ureters, stomach, small bowel loops, colon, and rectum are within normal limits. There is no evidence of focal lesions in the liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, adrenal glands, or significant lymphadenopathy.
